    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Quickfix: Debian Squeeze - eth0 not coming up at boot]]></title>
    <link href="http://blog.jbinto.ca//blog/2012/10/27/quickfix-debian-squeeze-eth0-not-coming-up-at-boot/"/>
    <updated>2012-10-27T10:39:00-04:00</updated>
    <id>http://blog.jbinto.ca//blog/2012/10/27/quickfix-debian-squeeze-eth0-not-coming-up-at-boot</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p><strong>Problem:</strong> After rebooting a remote Debian Squeeze server, the eth0 network
interface would not come up. <code>/etc/network/interfaces</code> was configured correctly.
The only way to get the network up was to run <code>ifconfig eth0 up</code> and
<code>dhclient eth0</code>.</p>

<p><strong>Configuration:</strong></p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span>/etc/network/interfaces </span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
<span class='line-number'>8</span>
<span class='line-number'>9</span>
<span class='line-number'>10</span>
<span class='line-number'>11</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='text'><span class='line'># Used by ifup(8) and ifdown(8). See the interfaces(5) manpage or
</span><span class='line'># /usr/share/doc/ifupdown/examples for more information.
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>auto lo
</span><span class='line'>iface lo inet loopback
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>auto eth0
</span><span class='line'>iface eth0 inet static
</span><span class='line'>address 1.2.3.4
</span><span class='line'>netmask 255.255.255.0
</span><span class='line'>gateway 1.2.3.1
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p></p>

<p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>

<p>The <code>ifupdown</code> package wasn&#8217;t installed for some reason (probably due to
upgrade issues).
<code>/etc/init.d/networking</code> fails silently when <code>ifup</code> can&#8217;t be found.</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='bash'><span class='line'><span class="nv">$ </span>apt-get install ifupdown
</span><span class='line'><span class="nv">$ </span>/etc/init.d/networking restart
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>

]]></content>
